JavaScript:
Light weight – simple syntax and semantics, quick and easy to learn.
Interpreted – line by line execution.
Scripting language for webpages and many non-browser environments.
Single threaded – not multithreaded because only one line can execute at a time.
Dynamic language – reads variable value in runtime.
Multi-paradigm – Object-oriented, imperative, and declarative style.
prototype - Class are implemented my methods.

Compilers used:
V8 – for chrome and node JS.
SpiderMonkey – for Firefox.


ECMA Script
•	After JavaScript is standardized my Europeans, it’s got a new name as ECMA Script(European Computer Manufacturers Association).
